Average runner time refers to the mean time taken by all runners in a team to complete the competition; 
Total time and average team time are collective measures of a team's performance; 
Team score represents the team's ranking or placement in the competition; 
A team size is the number of runners participating in the competition for that team; 
15 minutes is the threshold for average runner time used to filter competitions.

- Average time calculation assumes the time format is always 'HH:MM', where 'HH' represents hours and 'MM' represents minutes; 
- 'Final' result status indicates the considered results are conclusive and not subject to change; 
- Coach's experience is relevant for assessing team performance quality, with more experienced coaches potentially leading to better outcomes; 
- The ranking considers both speed (average time) and achievement (total score), providing a holistic view of team performance.
